
[1]pen

   PEN, n. [L. penna; pinna, a fin, that is, a shoot or point.]

   1. An instrument used for writing, usually made of the quill of some
   large fowl, but it may be of any other material.

   2. A feather, a wing. [Not used.]

     PEN, v.t. pret. and pp. penned. To write; to compose and commit to
                                   paper.

         PEN, n. A small inclosure for beasts, as for cows or sheep.

   PEN, v.t. pret. and pp. penned or pent. To shut in a pen; to confine in
      a small inclosure; to coop; to confine in a narrow place, usually
                     followed by up, which is redundant.
